properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 29 at 5:36AM AKST until January 30 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 7
inches. Winds gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Juneau.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to noon AKST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Snowy conditions could
impact the morning commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Confidence is poor, and anticipated high
winds occurring early could warm temperatures and lowering snow
totals.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO NOON AKST THURSDAY OF JUNEAU
